Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: simplecurry
Version: 1.12
Summary: Curried decorator
Home-page: https://github.com/grimborg/simplecurry
Author: Òscar Vilaplana
Author-email: dev@oscarvilaplana.cat
License: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.html
Description: Simplecurry’s ``curried`` provides a simple way to use curried functions in Python. There are alternative implementations, but they are unnecessarily complex.
        
        Example
        ~~~~~~~
        
        This is an example on how to use it::
        
            from simplecurry import curried
        
            @curried
            def add(a, b, c):
                return a + b + c
            
            add(1)(2)(3) # Returns 6
            add(1, 2)(3) # Returns 6
            add(1)(2, 3) # Returns 6
            add(1, 2, 3) # Returns 6
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
